[00:00] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'Welcome to the Hypershell X Tutorial Video In this video we will guide you through the steps to properly wear and use this cutting-edge PowerSuit Start by opening the package Take out the EPP Box and open it Check the items inside the box'

[00:14] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'Remove the partition film and insert the battery Peel off the protective film from the hip lever'

[00:39] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'Scan the QR Code in the User Manual to download the Hypershell+ App Register your account and log in for the first time'

[00:55] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'Enter body index in the App Adjust Hip Levers to the recommended width'

[01:18] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'Buckle Up the Hip Belt'

[01:53] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'Adjust the straps on each side individually one at a time to firmly tighten the hip belt Press the Slide Buttons to adjust the front strap position until you hear a click'

[02:05] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'ensuring the end of front straps are about 2 fingers\' width above your knees then buckle up the leg straps until you hear a click Tighten both ends of the leg straps'

[02:19] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'until they fit snugly around your thighs Finally make minor adjustments to both the hip and leg straps ensuring they\'re neither too loose nor too tight'

[02:31] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'Press the control button once'

[02:44] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'then long-press the button until the LEDs flashes Connect the device to your phone or other devices via Bluetooth The default mode after powering on is Eco Mode'

[02:56] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'which provides adaptable power for moderate activities like hiking To switch to Transparent Mode which pauses assistance single-click the control button Single-click again to return to Eco Mode'

[03:10] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'To enter Hyper Mode press and hold the control button for 2 seconds This mode provides dynamic power'

[03:22] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'for more intense activities like running or mountaineering To switch back to Eco Mode press and hold the button for another 2 seconds There are 4 levels under Eco and Hyper Mode Double-click to increase the power level'

[03:36] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'Triple-click to decrease the power level You can experience different modes and power levels to find your favourite state'

[03:49] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'Powered by AI MotionEngine Hypershell X can detect your posture and adjust the states of assistance in real time It\'s capable of recognizing 10 distinct motion states Discover even more features within the app!'

[04:04] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'We regularly introduce exciting new updates to enhance your experience Use the dashboard to easily switch modes and fine-tune assistance levels with precision Explore special modes like Fitness Mode'

[04:17] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'to tailor your experience to your goals For more specific needs dive into the MotionEngine section to adjust parameters such as assistive responsiveness creating a setup that\'s perfectly personalized to you Now let’s go over how to power off'

[04:32] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'and store your device Just like Power On press the control button once then long-press it until the device shuts down Begin by releasing the leg buckles Next'

[04:45] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'release the hip buckle while holding the hip lever to prevent the device from falling To charge the battery you can use any PD/QC charger by connecting it to the USB-C port on your Hypershell X Alternatively'

[05:04] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'you can use the 4-port charging hub to charge multiple batteries simultaneously For storage'

[05:16] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'Hypershell X can be folded into a compact size using soft straps First buckle up the hip belt and tighten it Second'

[05:29] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'Flip the leg straps over and loop them around the leg levers then buckle them up Then you can put it into your daily bags Thank you for watching!'

[05:44] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'If you have any questions feel free to reach out to our customer support team'
